<p><strong>Pinot Noir from Oregon or Burgundy</strong> creates another timeless combination, particularly with chicken prepared with earthy mushrooms or bacon. The wine's silky tannins won't overpower the meat, while its red fruit notes and often present forest floor undertones complement umami-rich preparations beautifully.</p>

